JOHANNESBURG -  Jason Rohde, former South African head of the property group Sotheby’s International Realty is expected back in the Western Cape High Court on Tuesday, where he is on trial for the alleged murder of his wife, Susan. Rhode is accused of murdering his wife Susan in their hotel room at the luxury Spier hotel outside Stellenbosch in July 2016. He denies killing his wife and claims that she committed suicide by hanging herself from the bathroom door. The State alleges he strangled her. READ: Rohde's fractured ribs made hanging herself unlikely: pathologist The multi-millionaire was arrested at his home in August 2016. Rohde, who had to pay R100,000 bail and provide a R1 million surety guarantee, was allowed to return home to Johannesburg at the end of August 2016. African News Agency